Hi, I'm wondering what is the semantics of confirmOffset and it's a bit hard for me to know why do we need a confirmOffset and what it stands for. Because I saw in ReputMessageService#doReput there is a code segment used confirmOffset
```
                if (DefaultMessageStore.this.getMessageStoreConfig().isDuplicationEnable()
                    && this.reputFromOffset >= DefaultMessageStore.this.getConfirmOffset()) {
                    break;
                }
```

So I'm wondering if a new confirmOffset impl would compatible with the semantics here.
Also the naming here is a bit confusing, as getConfirmOffset is returning timestamp like  `getMinTimestamp()`. Why we return a timestamp for an offset.
Thanks so much.
